claim.claim-text:
A folding golf cart having a lock device (3) to lock the golf cart in an extended state such that the golf cart cannot be folded, characterized in that the lock device comprises:
a brake pillar (34);
a locking piece (35); and
a button (32);
wherein the brake pillar is on one part and the locking piece is on another part of the golf cart and the two parts are arranged to move towards each other when unfolding the golf cart;

characterized in that

the locking piece (35) is arranged to provide a restriction through which the brake pillar is inserted during unfolding the cart, the locking piece (35) being rotated to a first position by abutment between the brake pillar and locking device wherein the restriction is widened so as to allow a portion of the brake pillar to pass and the locking piece is biased to rotate towards a second position wherein the restriction is narrowed to prevent withdrawal of the brake pillar (34); and

the button (32) is arranged to rotate the locking piece towards the first position to release the brake pillar from the restriction.
